body.description: OneSpace is a name you can trust for stylish and functional home and office furnishings. Finished in beautiful wood-grain melamine, the Eleanor Executive Desk is a handsome addition wherever you use it. This modern desk features hidden cord and wiring access in the rear of the large open hutch and includes a built-in USB and charger hub for convenient plug-in access. It’s designed to function as a traditional office work desk with 2 easy slide-out drawers up top and a deeper bottom drawer for heavier items. With its unique contemporary styling and modern tech-savvy conveniences, it’s the perfect executive office desk for completing both computer and noncomputer work.This sturdy desk weighs 79.5 lbs. and measures 47.24" W x 21.70" D x 34.70" H when assembled. It can support up to 110 lbs., making it an ideal storage desk for student textbooks, heavy files, or large business ledgers. With its available storage space and open desktop space, this modern office desk is perfect for use as a study desk, writing desk, or home computer desk. It can also serve as an aesthetic centerpiece to complete your room decor. No matter how you utilize this wooden desk with drawers, it’s sure to make your life a little more organized and comfortable.This desk is offered by OneSpace, part of the Comfort Products family. With a history dating back to 1919 and headquarters in America’s distribution capital of Memphis, TN, Comfort Products specializes in providing affordable brands for better living.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Choice, Great Price
reviews.reviewText: I love this desk, it's appearance, the sturdiness, the capacity of the 3 drawers and the attached outlet/USB port. The assembly directions were mostly clear and concise. It is extremely heavy. I opened the package where it was delivered inside my door, removed all the pieces from the carton into the room I planned to use it, and that's where I assembled it. I would never have been able to move it on my own across a carpeted floor. I did attach some felt floor savers under the legs so it wouldn't scratch up my wood floor, and they make it easier to move it around in my office.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Pandemic effects caused a transition in employment opportunities as most people experienced. In our situation we did not want to substitute quality for convenience. These desks did just that! We bought 2, so as to match and have a heavy and durable piece. The cost wasn't bad at all compared to less expensive and less quality alternatives. Ease of installation, quality, craftsmanship and features makes this 9/10 product. However, if you like EXTREMELY simple installation, this may fall outside your preference. Requires a few hours and some patience/intuitiveness BUT worth the end result!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Good price

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy but need two people
reviews.reviewText: I Love this desk. The color is exactly what I wanted. It's more sturdy and heavier than I was expecting, but that's just what you want in a desk. For the most part one person can put it together. However, you definitely need two people for just one step when you're putting the top onto the legs. I tried by myself and ended up breaking it where the screws insert, and had to use super glue with the screws to add extra support. But everything else can be done with just one person.I highly recommend this desk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pretty neat desk, it's kind of small but good enough for most people.
reviews.reviewText: I like the desk, it suits my needs, isn't crazy good wow but is probably good enough for an entry level desk. You get what you pay for, and it's decent for most people. Something important to note is that the hole for the wires will not fit adapter blocks because it is too small, in case you want to slip a charger wire through the back.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 25, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this desk for my daughter to work at. I was honestly a little scared due to the reviews that I read, however, even with the pictures posted of people who had problems, it looked like one that I could adapt or fix if needed. Ordered it, and it arrived via UPS, when I went on the porch to get it noticed a hole in the exterior box. Upon opening it I found that the interior boxes were still in tact. Took everything out and inspected each piece, and there wasn't any damage. Counted all the pieces, and components and they were all there. This process took me about 15 minutes.I then set to work setting it up, and timed myself. The instructions made sense, and followed their flow, it took me about 45 minutes to set it up and it was sturdy with no gaps or loose pieces. You will want to use a hand driven philips screw driver rather than any power tools. Also when assembling the side pieces I found it easier to assemble them flat on the ground with the legs at the side.Overall, for a assemble by cams and dowels furniture it is pretty good. If I need another one of this size I would purchase it again.
